se to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Default value: 0. Value range: [0, 1]","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange"]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://com.mapbox.MapboxMaps/documentation/MapboxMaps/FillExtrusionLayer/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange":{"kind":"symbol","title":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","url":"\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"text":">?","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled.","type":"text"